<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,532,438,464]" box="[151,532,438,464]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,532,438,464]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,532,438,464]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Thor, 1899" authorityName="Thor" authorityYear="1899" box="[238,532,438,464]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Kongsbergia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,391,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Kongsbergia</emphasis>
Thor, 
<number box="[473,532,438,464]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="1899.0">1899</number>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,509,786]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
In contrast to 
<taxonomicName box="[320,395,510,533]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Aturus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[320,395,510,533]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Aturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, species-diagnostic characters may (but not must!) be found in both sexes in shape and setation of the palp. In many cases, these are helpful for reciprocal attribution of sexes. 
<collectingCountry box="[1140,1171,545,569]" name="American Samoa" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">As</collectingCountry>
compared with 
<taxonomicName box="[1354,1429,545,568]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Aturus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1354,1429,545,568]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Aturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, sexual dimorphism in 
<taxonomicName box="[402,545,581,605]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Kongsbergia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[402,545,581,605]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Kongsbergia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
involves to a lesser degree the dorsal idiosoma (here, sexes differ occasionally in shape of dorsal setae and surface sculpturation), but often also the shape of palp segments. 
<collectingCountry box="[1239,1270,618,642]" name="American Samoa" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">As</collectingCountry>
in 
<taxonomicName box="[1310,1385,618,641]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Aturus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1310,1385,618,641]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Aturus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the male IV-L is strikingly modified for holding the female during mating: IV-L- 
<number box="[1035,1047,653,678]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="6.0">6</number>
can be shut against the preceding segment and there received in a longitudinal groove and fixed by a proximoventral processus of IV-L- 
<number box="[1345,1357,689,714]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="5.0">5</number>
. Three characteristically modified ventral setae of IV-L- 
<number box="[710,722,725,750]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" value="5.0">5</number>
are here addressed as &quot;proximal&quot;, &quot;central&quot; and &quot;distal&quot; setae. All treated species belong to subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[588,732,761,785]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Kongsbergia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[588,732,761,785]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Kongsbergia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[738,799,762,785]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, characterized by the I-L without sexual modifications.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
